Definition 2.13. (compare with [Mar91], [Mar94]) The partition algebra $FP_{n}(t)$ is defined to be the endomorphism algebra $\text{End}_{\underline{\operatorname{Re}}\!\operatorname{p}_{0}(S_{t};F)}([n])$.
Definition 3.26. The hook length of a fixed box in a Young diagram $\lambda$ is the number of boxes in $\lambda$ which are either directly below or directly to the right of the fixed box, counting the fixed box itself once. Given a Young diagram $\lambda$ let $P_{\lambda}$ denote the unique polynomial such that $P_{\lambda}(d)=\frac{d!}{\prod(\text{hook lengths of }\lambda(d))}$ for every integer $d\geq 2|\lambda|$.
Definition 5.1. For $t\in F$ and a Young diagram $\lambda=(\lambda_{1},\lambda_{2},\ldots)$, set $\mu_{\lambda}(t):=(t-|\lambda|,\lambda_{1}-1,\lambda_{2}-2,\ldots).$ For Young diagrams $\lambda$ and $\lambda^{\prime}$ write $\mu_{\lambda}(t)=(\mu_{0},\mu_{1},\ldots)$ and $\mu_{\lambda^{\prime}}(t)=(\mu^{\prime}_{0},\mu^{\prime}_{1},\ldots)$. We write $\lambda\stackrel{{\scriptstyle t}}{{\sim}}\lambda^{\prime}$ whenever there exists a bijection $\tau:\mathbb{Z}_{\geq 0}\to\mathbb{Z}_{\geq 0}$ with $\mu_{i}=\mu^{\prime}_{\tau(i)}$ for all $i\geq 0$.
