Definition 4.5. For $t\in F$ and integers $r>0$, and $n\geq 0$, define $\omega_{n}^{r}(t)\in FP_{n}(t)$ as follows. Using the basis $\{x_{\pi}\}$ for $FP_{n}(t)$ defined in (2.1), set $\omega_{n}^{r}(t)=\sum_{\pi\in P_{n,n}}q_{\pi,r,t}x_{\pi}$ where, using the notation set up in Proposition 4.3, $q_{\pi,r,t}=\left\{\begin{array}[]{ll}0,&\text{if }S(\pi,r,d)=0\text{ for all % integers }d>1,\\ \frac{(r-a+c-1)!}{(r-a+b)!}\prod\limits_{k=1}^{r+b-a}(t-r-b+k),&\text{% otherwise.}\end{array}\right.$
